<p>I'm having some difficulties changing the Android standard Switch width. I managed to change its height but not its width. I did something like this:</p>  <pre><code>                &lt;Switch                     android:id="@+id/coating_video_switch"                     android:layout_width="wrap_content"                     android:layout_height="wrap_content"                     android:gravity="center_vertical"                     android:checked="false"                     android:switchMinWidth="40dp"                     android:minWidth="40dp"                     android:minHeight="40dp"                     android:textSize="5sp"                     android:layout_margin="1dp"                     android:textOff="fo"                     android:textOn="no"                     android:thumb="@drawable/thumb"                     android:track="@drawable/track"                     android:layout_below="@+id/coating_lbl_video_mode"                     android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I tried to change the <strong>switchMinWidth</strong> 's value but nothing happens. Setting the <strong>width</strong> of the <strong>widget</strong> and <strong>maxWidth</strong> doesn't help because it just <strong>"crops"</strong> the switch meaning that the <strong>thumb and track have the same size</strong> but you are able to see just a part(middle) of them. I follow other threads regarding this issue which say that the <strong>drawable elements are actually changing the width of the switch</strong>. I've created 2 drawable elements(track and thumb png files) and <strong>give them different sizes in pixels but still nothing happens</strong>. I also changed the textSize value but the text never changes. What am I missing here? Thank you for your time and for any tip!</p>